<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd" MadCap:lastBlockDepth="4" MadCap:lastHeight="757" MadCap:lastWidth="936" MadCap:conditions="Products.Central">
    <body>
        <ul>
            <li MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet14,Snippets.Snippet13"><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Colored Versus Grayed Out </span>If a user's avatar and name appear in color, it means that user is active in the system. If they are grayed out, it means that user has been deactivated.</li>
            <li MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet15"><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Colored Versus Grayed Out </span>If a user's avatar appears in color, it means that user is active in the system. If it is grayed out, it means that user has been deactivated.</li>
            <li MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet13,Snippets.Snippet14,Snippets.Snippet15"><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">User Card </span>If you hover over the avatar or name, a user card displays. This user card lets you take a few quick actions related to that user (view profile, set permissions, send message, assign task, view activity).</li>
            <li MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet16"><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Team Card </span>If you hover over the avatar or team name, a team card displays. This team card lets you take a few quick actions related to that team (view profile, edit profile, send message, view activity).</li>
            <li MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet13"><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">User Profile </span>If you click on the avatar or name, the User Profile dialog opens. See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Users/Viewing_User_Profiles.htm">Viewing User Profiles</MadCap:xref>.</li>
            <li>
                <p MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet13,Snippets.Snippet14,Snippets.Snippet15"><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Avatar </span>If a user has selected an image, it is displayed next to the name. If a user has not selected an image, that user's initials are shown instead.</p>
                <p MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet13,Snippets.Snippet14,Snippets.Snippet15">In addition, decorations provide further clues about the user. First a crown at the upper-left of the avatar indicates the user is an administrator with "Manage Users" permission. A small circle at the bottom-right indicates whether the user is online (green=online; yellow=online but has been idle for at least 30 minutes; gray=offline).</p>
                <p MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet13">
                    <img src="../../Images/user_avatars1.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth100Percent" />
                </p>
                <p MadCap:conditions="General.Future">xxx created by image -- condition with snippet 14</p>
                <p MadCap:conditions="General.Future">xxx users (all on team) image -- condition with snippet 15</p>
            </li>
            <li MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet16">
                <p><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Avatar </span>If an image has been assigned to the team, it is displayed next to the team name. If an image has not been assigned, a default image is displayed instead.</p>
                <p MadCap:conditions="General.Future">image xxx</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </body>
</html>